Let me help you solve this building block task by analyzing the images:

Main Target Image Analysis:
- The target structure is a two-layer building composed of two different block types
- Bottom layer: A red arch/curved block
- Top layer: An orange/reddish triangular/peaked block

Block Dictionary Analysis:
- Block 1: Red curved arch block (bottom layer)
- Block 9: Red rectangular block (bottom layer base)
- Block 11 or 12: Orange triangular/peaked block (top layer)

Assembly Instructions:
{
   Step1: Move block with index 9 (red rectangular base)
   Step2: Move block with index 1 (red curved arch block)
   Step3: Move block with index 11 (orange triangular/peaked block)
}

This sequence will recreate the target structure by:
1. Placing the red rectangular base
2. Adding the red curved arch block on top of the base
3. Completing the structure with the orange triangular block on top of the arch

The assembly follows the exact block orientations shown in the dictionary and matches the target image precisely.
